FT  22 SEP 92 / China to sell uranium to Japan
Tokyo Electric Power, the Japanese power company, yesterday announced an
agreement to import 250 short tons of uranium concentrate from China, the
first agreement of its kind involving the Chinese product, Robert Thomson
reports from Tokyo. The agreement, which calls for delivery over five years,
starting next year, is part of the Japanese power industry's strategy of
diversifying its sources of uranium.
